<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Economic Security Meeting Studies Issues </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001213994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1715 
GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1001213994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 10 Jan -- The first session of the 
inter-departmental commission of the Russian Security Council 
for economic security took place today. By decree of the 
Russian president, Andrey Zverev, head of the economic 
department of the Russian Federation governmental apparatus, has 
been appointed the commission's chairman. Questions connected 
with working out a state doctrine of economic security, the 
progress of the economic reforms in the country, and other 
matters were examined. 
  Heads of ministries and departments reepresented in the 
commission took part in the session. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

