<H3> <TI>   Premier Appoints Acting Ministers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1001134094 Tallinn BNS in English 1059 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1001134094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, Jan 10, BNS -- Estonian Prime Minister 
Mart Laar in his ruling No. 10-k today sacked Economics Minister 
Toomas Sildmae and appointed Arvo Niitenberg, the energy 
minister without portfolio, as acting economics minister. Laar 
in the same ruling appointed Minister of Justice Kaido Kama 
acting finance minister. 

</TEXT>

