<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deportation of Russian Generals Disrupts Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001164694 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1600 GMT 10 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1001164694 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to an order by Andrejs Rucs, the head of 
the local government of the Vidzeme district of Riga, two 
generals of the North-Western Group of Russian Forces were 
detained and deported to the state border today. The 
above-mentioned persons were detained this morning when 
representatives of the local government of Vidzeme district came 
to a Russian Army facility in Riga to take it over. 
  Andrejs Rucs spoke to Latvian President Guntis Ulmanis about 
today's incident and this issue was also discussed at a session 
of the National Security Council today. Rucs added that the 
fact that the generals were detained on a day talks were 
scheduled between Russian and Latvian delegations was a 
coincidence. He expressed an opinion that the incident might 
cause the Saeima and the government to demand finally from the 
Russian side a concrete timetable for the army withdrawal. 
  Sergey Zotov, the head of the Russian delegation, arriving 
for the talks on army withdrawal today, said that the talks 
could not begin until the above-mentioned incident is clarified. 
  Martins Virsis, the head of the Latvian delegation for talks 
with Russia, while waiting for the Russian delegation on the 
airfield, commented that the incident was a deliberate attempt 
to disrupt the talks. The Latvian side will correspondingly 
[words indistinct], (?said) Virsis. 

</TEXT>

