<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Amends Laws, Dismisses Rucs </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101104094 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0900 GMT 
11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1101104094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] An emergency session of the Latvian cabinet was 
held during the night from Monday to Tuesday [10-11 January]. 
It decided to punish those guilty of the provocations against 
Russian military personnel and diplomats. [passage omitted] 
  The cabinet adopted a number of amendments to laws making it 
possible for the government to dismiss leaders of local 
government authorities who break the law. At the same time, 
Andrejs Rucs was dismissed and criminal proceedings were 
instituted against him on charges of exceeding his authority and 
illegal detention of people, Interfax reported. 

</TEXT>

