<H3> <TI>   Paper Publishes Data on Defense Forces </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1001152694 Riga LETA in English 1420 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1001152694 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga LETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Review of the Latvian Press"] </F>
  [Text] The newspaper "NEATKARIGA CINA" publishes the data 
concerning the Latvian Army. At present, the personnel of the 
Latvian Defence Forces consists of 1,500 soldiers and 150 
officers. 600 soldiers and 30 officers serve in the naval forces 
and 150 soldiers and 30 officers - in the air forces. 3.8 
thousand soldiers and 340 officers guard the Latvian frontiers. 
On the whole, 6 thousand soldiers and 550 officers make up the 
Latvian Army. 15 ships are at the Latvian Army's disposal. 
Only 9 of them are cleared of planes: "-2" and two-410". 
[sentence as received] Only one of them is ready for action. 4 
helicopters out of 6 are ready for action. This year, 1.8 per 
cent from the budget funds are supposed to be allocated for the 
needs of the Latvian defence forces. 

</TEXT>

