<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Brazauskas Statement on Integration </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001191394 Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network in Lithuanian 
1700 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1001191394 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Lithuanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement to the press issued by President Algirdas </F>
Brazauskas -- read by announcer] 
  [Text] Having recently declared a wish to join NATO, 
Lithuania is observing the NATO summit in Brussels with great 
interest. 
  I welcome the invitation to participate in the program 
called 
Partnership for Peace which was presented this morning by the 
heads of the NATO states and partners in cooperation. This is 
the road for Lithuania for complete integration into NATO 
political and military structures. 
  Lithuania looks positively at the efforts made by NATO to 
respond to the changes in Europe and in the world and to ensure 
a stable entrance into the 21st century. 
  I believe that the document defining the nature of 
partnership signed by Lithuania and NATO will be a consistent 
supplement to the efforts made by Lithuania to set up a 
democratically controlled military force and relevant relations 
between military and civilian institutions. 
  I have entrusted the government and the leaders of relevant 
ministries to take the necessary steps and get ready to sign the 
document on partnership, to assess the supplies, the resources, 
and the forces, and to prepare a program of measures through the 
implementation of which all the common objectives of partnership 
will be achieved. 

</TEXT>

