<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   No Intention to Establish Contact With Serb Krajina </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001203294 Moscow Radio Moscow World Service in English 
1900 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1001203294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Moscow World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Russian Federation does not intend to establish 
official contacts with Serbian Krajina. The statement was made 
by a high-ranking Foreign Ministry official in Moscow. 
  According to sources in Belgrade, a delegation of the self- 
proclaimed Republic of Serbian Krajina intends to arrive in 
Moscow on Tuesday. The republic is a Serbian-populated area in 
Croatia, conflicting with Zagreb, and favoring unification of 
Serbian lands into a separate state. 
  A Russian diplomat said such a republic does not exist for 
Russia. Russia maintains contacts with Croatia, which is a 
member of the United Nations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

