<H3> <TI>   Churkin Meets Slovak Officials in Bratislava </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001224994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1830 
GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1001224994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [by ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Rzhevskiy] </F>
  [Text] Bratislava, 10 Jan -- Russian Deputy Foreign 
Minister Vitaliy Churkin met Slovak Republic Foreign Minister 
Jozef Moravcik here today. Questions relating to the 
development of security structures for Europe were looked at in 
depth, including NATO, along with the main trends in political 
and economic relations between European states. After 
expressing, on the whole, mutual satisfaction with the first 
year in which links have been developed between Russia and 
Slovakia, the two spoke in favor of developing them in all ways 
possible. 
  European integration was discussed during the meeting 
between 
V. Churkin and Slovak Deputy Prime Minister Jozef Prokes. 

