<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Baku Reports Front Line Details </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1001215694 Baku TURAN in English 1708 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1001215694 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku, January 10 (TURAN)--The Defense Ministry of 
Azerbaijan says that yesterday's fighting in the front continues. 
  Units of Armenian Armed Forces are attempting to intercept 
the initiative. Last morning they launched an offensive towards 
the north of the city of Agdam. Earlier they bombarded 
positions of the Azeri Army from "Grad" power-plants. The 
Armenian's attack was repelled with return firing. Having 
sustained losses, Armenian units retreated to their positions. 
  Fighting in the southern section of the front continues. The 
Azeri Army reached the Goradiz-Fizuli Highway. Yesterday the 
Armenians abandoned a number of important positions and Azeri 
Army units were able to reach the city of Fizuli. 
  The enemy has withdrawn from the village of Lulasaz and a 
predominant hill-top in the northern section of the frontline. 
The fighting near the Sarsang Reservoir continues. 
  For the past two days the Armenian Army lost 3 tanks, 2 BMPs 
and approximately 50 soldiers, say military sources. 

</TEXT>

