<H3> <TI>   Mercenaries Paid 500,000 Rubles </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0801144394 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1400 GMT 
8 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0801144394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to POWs from CIS countries captured in 
Karabakh, Azerbaijan pays each of the mercenaries fighting on 
its side 500,000 Russian rubles a month. For carrying out 
especially important military assignments, a soldier of fortune 
receives additionally up to 10,000 US dollars. Member of 
parliament of the Nagornyy Karabakh Republic writer (Zuriy 
Balayan) has given this information to SNARK agency. Apart from 
this, nearly 1,500 Afghan modjaheddin are also fighing on the 
Azeri side, which is not even being denied by Kabul. Balayan 
expressed his surprise by the total absence of any reaction from 
the Russian leadership to the recent television report on a 
group of mercenaries recruited in Ivanovo that was departing for 
Azerbaijan. This was an IMA-press report. 

</TEXT>

