<H3> <TI>   Strict Terms Imposed for Joining Ruble Zone </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001173094 Tbilisi IBERIA in Georgian 1450 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1001173094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi IBERIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Georgian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi, 10 Jan -- IBERIA news agency learned from 
reliable sources that Georgia might join the ruble zone in the 
immediate future. Russia is putting forward quite strict terms 
for this; in particular, it is ready to accept Georgia in this 
zone provided Georgia refuses that part of the foreign 
countries' debt which, after the disintegration of the Soviet 
Union, belonged to it, and refuses foreign assets, gold mines 
(if such are available or will be available in future), and 
independent credit emissions. 
  According to the reports by the same source, Russia may also 
demand that nominees for the posts of finance minister and 
president of the national bank be chosen only with Russia's 
participation. 

</TEXT>

