<H3> <TI>   Body Said in Zviadist Village </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1101105694 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 11 Jan 94 First 
Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM1101105694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [INTERFAX report: "Gamsakhurdia's Body Is in a Village </F>
Controlled by the Zviadists"] 
  [Text] The body of Georgian ex-president Zviad 
Gamsakhurdia is in the village of Dzhikhashkari in 
Tsalendzhikhskiy Rayon in Western Georgia. 
  This was stated at the Georgian Internal Affairs Ministry 
press center. According to a staffer of the press center, the 
village is under the control of armed Zviadists who are 
demanding that international experts come. Z. Gamsakhurdia died 
on the night of 31 December-1 January in a settlement in Western 
Georgia. It is believed that he committed suicide. 

</TEXT>

