<H3> <TI>   Ryabov Presents Election Figures to Federation Council </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101120494 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1000 GMT 
11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1101120494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Chairman of the Central Electoral Commission Nikolay 
Ryabov has reported that 58,187,000 people, or 54 percent of the 
total electorate, took part in the vote on the draft new 
Constitution of the Russian Federation. A total of 32,937,000, 
or more than 58 percent, voted in favor of the Constitution. 
After the elections, 150 complaints were registered and some of 
these had been submitted for examination in the courts. The 
election campaign cost 160 billion rubles. Nikolay Ryabov also 
reported that representatives of 29 nationalities had been 
elected to the Federation Council. Russians make up 76 percent 
of the total number of deputies in the upper chamber. 

</TEXT>

