<H3> <TI>   First Session of Duma Opened by Lukava </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101103394 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0900 GMT 
11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1101103394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Our correspondent Yevgeniy Zherebenkov reports 
on proceedings in the State Duma: 
  [Zherebenkov] The first session of the lower house of 
parliament, the State Duma, was opened by Lukava, senior deputy 
and representative of the Liberal Democratic Party. Then, at 
the proposal of the faction of the Communist Party of Russia, 
the deputies stood in memory of the victims of the October 1993 
events. [passage omitted: Chernomyrdin conveyed Yeltsin's 
greetings to the Duma and spoke on government's plans] 
  The deputies also listened to a report by Aleksandr 
Ivanchenko, deputy chairman of the Central Electoral Commission, 
on the results of the 12 December elections, and they have now 
started work on the formation of temporary working bodies, a 
temporary secretariat, a tellers' commission, and a commission 
for monitoring electronic voting. 

