<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Troops Come Under Attack on Afghan Border </TI></H3>
<H4>   `Militants' Attack Russian Guards </H4>
<F P=102> LD1001132494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1136 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1001132494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tajik militants attacked Russian border guards three 
times over the weekend. As a Russian officer reported to 
Interfax, the rear of the 12th outpost of Moscow's Border Unit 
came under fire from mortars, recoilless guns, and rocket 
installations. 
  A Russian border outpost on Turg mountain and Parvar and 
Arvar villages were also attacked. The servicemen suffered no 
casualties. Counter strikes were delivered on the militants' 
positions. 
  The officer also reported an attempt by a gang of militants 
to break through a border section guarded by the 3rd outpost of 
the Pyanj Border Unit. After a clash with guards, the gang 
retreated back into Afghanistan. 
  Stepped-up militant activity is linked to better weather 
conditions on the Tajik-Afghan border. 

</TEXT>

