<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on NATO Membership Request </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001131494 Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network in Lithuanian 
1000 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1001131494 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Lithuanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Lithuanian President Algirdas Brazauskas speaking 
at a news conference this morning touched upon the NATO summit 
in Brussels, in addition to other issues. 
  Here is correspondent Audrius Baciulis with a report from 
the 
news conference and about other events which took place at the 
Lithuanian Seimas. 
  [Baciulis] Algirdas Brazauskas said that today a response is 
expected from Brussels concerning Lithuania's wish to join NATO. 
He also said that when NATO received the written membership 
application from Lithuania, it was immediately disseminated 
among all its sixteen members. According to the president, not 
all the states had submitted written applications asking to join 
NATO. 
  In the president's view, although there will be no specific 
date given from which Lithuania will become member of NATO, 
Lithuania nevertheless supports the Partnership for Peace 
initiative proposed by the USA which, according to Algirdas 
Brazauskas, is a starting point in the process of joining NATO. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-55739 </DOCNO>
