<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Federation Council Hears Electoral Commission Report </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101095894 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0900 GMT 
11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1101095894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by special correspondent Yelena Kuznetsova from the </F>
Federation Council] 
  [Text] At the proposal of Boris Nikolayevich Yeltsin, the 
first session of the Federation Council following the elections 
is being chaired by senior deputy Yuriy Chernichenko, who 
announced that the first question on the standing orders would 
be a report by Nikolay Ryabov. 
  The chairman of the Central Electoral Commission reported on 
the results of the elections and called on the deputies to 
justify the high trust of the people. The next issue on the 
standing orders was the election of the credentials commission 
and recognition of the authority of the deputies. The main 
question on the agenda is the election of working bodies and of 
the chairman of the Federation Council and his deputies, as well 
as the formation of committees. 
  The house will elect yet another commission today from among 
the deputies to conduct the secret nomination of candidates for 
the post of chairman of the Federation Council. They will be 
responsible for the preparation of the voting paper. Each 
deputy will be given one voting paper which will be filled in in 
a booth for secret voting. In accordance with the rules, only 
one name may be entered for the post of chairman of the 
Federation Council. As a result of the secret nominations, the 
tellers' commission will draw up a report which will be signed 
by all members of the tellers' commission and confirmed by the 
Federation Council. 

</TEXT>

