<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Black Sea Fleet Criticism of Ukraine Navy Activities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101164594 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1336 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1101164594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sevastopol -- On 11 January, the press center of the 
Black Sea Fleet made public a statement which says in 
particular: "For the past two months, the Ukrainian Navy Command 
has been making unilateral attempts to resubordinate all Black 
Sea Fleet naval engineering service units deployed in the 
fleet's distant garrisons. Following recent unlawful actions in 
respect of the Black Sea Fleet naval engineering service 
departments in Odessa and Nikolayev, another action has been 
staged, aimed at having the Izmail region's personnel swear 
allegiance to Ukraine." 
  The press center of the Black Sea Fleet affirms that the 
fleet's group of units deployed in Izmail has virtually found 
itself under economic blockade. To normalize the situation and 
prevent further negative developments, the Black Sea Fleet 
Command has called for wisdom on the part of the Ukrainian Navy 
Command and voiced the opinion that it is necessary to wait 
until the Black Sea Fleet issues are settled by the Russian and 
Ukrainian presidents in a civilized manner. The Black Sea Fleet 
leadership has sent relevant documents on the situation in 
Izmail to the Ukrainian and Russian defense ministries. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

