<H3> <TI>   Leaders Arrive in Nukus </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201114694 Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network in Russian 
1000 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1201114694 </F>
<F P=104>  Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Imamali Rakhmanov, the head of state and chairman of 
the Supreme Council of Tajikistan who has arrived in Nukus, the 
Uzbek town, to take part in the work of the conference of the 
heads of Central Asian states and Russia on the problems of the 
Aral Sea, met with President Nursultan Nazarbayev of Kazakhstan. 
  Issues related to bilateral relations between Tajikistan and 
Kazakhstan have been discussed during the course of the meeting, 
which was held in an atmosphere of friendship. 
  A meeting between Tajik head of state Rakhmanov and 
President 
Islam Karimov of Uzbekistan took place in Nukus the same day [11 
January]. Bilateral relations between Tajikistan and Uzbekistan 
were discussed during the course of the meeting. 

</TEXT>

