<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Lauds Partnership for Peace Plan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1101164694 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 1525 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1101164694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement issued by the Ministry of Foreign Affairs in Kiev </F>
on 11 January] 
  [Text] The highest level meeting of NATO member states in 
Brussels has adopted the Partnership for Peace program. This 
document includes an appeal to former members of the Warsaw Pact 
and other European countries to participate in the program. The 
appeal of NATO member countries has been adopted at a difficult 
time, when some parts of the continent are sowing the seeds of 
conflict, and the majority of Central and East European 
countries are alarmed by the lack of structural mechanisms for 
security in this region. 
  Ukraine believes that the proposal of NATO countries to 
implement the Partnership for Peace program is a timely and 
broad-minded step in the right direction which will enable all 
interested countries to begin practical work on concrete 
political and military cooperation with NATO. Ukraine sees 
great interest in the development of such cooperation, and will 
cooperate with NATO and its member countries to the full extent 
within the framework of the Partnership for Peace program. 
Ukraine embraces with understanding the NATO initiative, which 
does not draw new lines of partition in Europe, while leaving 
the door to NATO open and serving as an instrument to gradually 
expand the organization eastward. Ukraine thinks that NATO is 
able to play a serious role in developing a reliable and 
all-embracing system of European security; Ukraine is ready to 
make a considerable contribution to the development of new 
architecture of security. The active participation of Ukraine 
in the "Partnership for Peace" program will assist in this 
process. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

