<H3> <TI>   Clinton Scheduled for Short Stopover in Kiev </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201105694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1017 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1201105694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Efim Schwarzmann] </F>
  [Text] Kiev January 12 TASS -- President Bill Clinton is 
due to arrive in Kiev, capital of Ukraine at 19.00 p.m. on 
Wednesday, despite fears that his "hastily-arranged stopover in 
Kiev could prove tougher than he thought" by thick fog which 
could make his landing difficult in the Ukrainian capital. 
  Sources from among the Ukrainian presidential staff told 
ITAR- TASS Clinton's stop-over will last for about two 
and-a-half hours. 
  The American and Ukrainian presidents are expected to 
discuss 
bilateral relations, military political problems and 
international security. 
  After the talks, President Clinton will board Air Force One 
en route to Moscow. President Leonid Kravchuk will join his and 
President Yeltsin in the Kremlin on January 14 for a trilateral 
summit which is expected to culminate in the signing of 
documents, which will ease tension in relations of the three 
countries. 

</TEXT>

