<H3> <TI>   Party Leader Criticizes Clinton's `Diktat' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201102694 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 0753 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1201102694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, 11 Jan -- Serhiy Plachynda, the chairman of 
the Peasant Democratic Party of Ukraine [SelDPU] has stated that 
U.S. President Bill Clinton's declaration that a trilateral 
agreement on nuclear weapons is to be signed in Moscow, is none 
other than a diktat and that it grossly interferes in Ukraine's 
internal affairs. 
  "Clinton ought to think about the fact that Ukrainian 
nuclear 
missiles are a guarantor of peace worldwide, rather than just 
for Ukraine, as well as for Europe and America itself," said the 
SelDPU chairman. 
  "If Zhirinovskiy does come to power, he will not be 
fastidious in either utterances or actions, which is why there 
must be a deterrent, which is what Ukraine's nuclear weapons 
are. After a considerable section of Russians have followed 
Zhirinovskiy, having opted for fascism, to make such statements 
as that by Clinton is quite outrageous," SelDPU Chairman 
Plachynda pointed out. 

</TEXT>

