<H3> <TI>   Nationalists: `We Do Not Believe American Promises' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101180094 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 1551 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1101180094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, 11 Jan -- "The position of the Congress of 
Ukrainian Nationalists on the question of nuclear weapons 
remains unchanged: for a nonnuclear Ukraine but in a nonnuclear 
world," stressed Mykhaylo Ratushnyy, member of the Congress of 
Ukrainian Nationalists leadership in an interview with a UNIAR 
correspondent. "In connection with the fact that the world 
around us is not nonnuclear, we are against signing an agreement 
between Clinton, Kravchuk, and Yeltsin." Mr. Ratushnyy noted 
that the Ukraine Republican Party considers the signing of an 
agreement on depriving Ukraine of its nuclear arsenal to be a 
betrayal of Ukrainian interests. "We do not believe American 
promises. America looks after its own interests first and 
foremost, and the Ukrainian Government should look after its 
Ukrainian interests, which it does not do." 

</TEXT>

