<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Crimean Speaker: Only Russia Can Guarantee Stability </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101192094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1645 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1101192094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Crimea should not be allowed to turn into the 
hunting ground of political terror or another war zone in the 
former USSR, Nikolay Bagrov, chairman of the Crimean parliament, 
told INTERFAX-Ukraine. In his view, Russia alone can guarantee 
stability in the region. "The Crimea cannot be rescued outside 
an alliance with Russia or peaceful reintegration into our 
historic Motherland," he said. 
  Bagrov also said that a campaign designed to discredit the 
Russian Party of the Crimea and himself as a candidate had been 
launched in the runup to the presidential elections that are 
scheduled to be held in the Crimea on January 16. 
  He complained that once he refused to drop out of the 
presidential race or call on his supporters to vote for another 
candidate, "certain political forces resorted to psychological 
terror" against him threatening to kill him, his family and 
friends. 
  The Russian Party leader thinks that the opponents of a 
Russian Crimea will not stop at criminal methods. He said: "I 
had to call officially on the state authorities of the Crimean 
Republic, Ukraine and the Russian Federation to prevent turning 
the Crimean general elections into a pretext for political 
terror or violence which could provoke an explosion or armed 
conflict." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

