<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Violence in Crimean Election Campaign Increases </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101163994 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in English 
0100 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1101163994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Our sources in Simferopol reported the Crimean 
presidential election campaign is increasingly assuming a 
scandalous and very physically violent nature with the 
contestants growingly relying on fist arguments. Thus last 
weekend witnessed a meeting of the Russian Party's activists, 
who demanded to recall their party leader, Sergey Shuvaynikov's 
candidature, accusing him of attempting to conceal the sources 
of his campaign financing and embezzlement. A few hours later 
three unidentified persons broke into the apartment of Russian 
Society chairman (Anatoliy Los), whose voice was among the 
loudest to accuse Shuvaynikov, took him to the street and beat 
him up. According to some other members of the Russian Party 
Political Council, they were threatened with physical violence, 
too. 

</TEXT>

