<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kiev City Approves State Secrets Protection Statute </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1201111694 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 0900 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1201111694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Ukrainian Cabinet of Ministers has approved a 
statute of the Kiev Oblast and City Board for Protection of 
State Secrets in Press and Other Mass Media. It was decreed 
that the board is a local body of the State Secret Protection 
Committee, as well as a part of the oblast administration due to 
the principle of dual subordination. The primary task of the 
board is the protection of state secrets and secret information 
in printed sources and other means of mass media including 
papers, journals, books, television and radio programs, 
documentary films, and exhibitions, as well as textual, audio, 
and audiovisual materials destined for shipment abroad, 
disclosure of which can harm military, scientific, 
technological, and economic interests of Ukraine. The board 
will give consultative assistance to local authorities, 
organizations, enterprises, publishing houses, mass media, and 
expert commissions in order to prevent the disclosure of state 
secrets and secret information in materials, which are being 
prepared for publication, broadcasting, or shipment abroad. The 
board is not entitled to control the ideological contents of 
those materials. The board carries out its activity on the 
basis of normative documents adopted for protection of state 
secrets and secret information in the press and other mass media. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

