<F P=106> [By BELINFORM correspondent Vladimir Glod for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Minsk January 11 TASS -- A delegation of the 
Belarusian Parliament led by its Speaker Stanislav Shushkevich 
is leaving for Moscow on Tuesday night for talks with Russian 
President Boris Yeltsin due to begin on Wednesday. 
  Shushkevich pointed out that "the forthcoming meeting is not 
spontaneous, but was thoroughly prepared." In Moscow, the sides 
are to discuss strategic issues of their interaction in the 
economic and other spheres. The sides are to specify their 
positions in the run up to the U.S. President Bill Clinton's 
visit to Moscow and Minsk. 
  The Belarusian delegation to the talks with Yeltsin includes 
several members of the presidium of the Belarusian Parliament, 
Vice-Premier Vladimir Zalomai, Chairman of the board of the 
Belarusian National Bank Stanislav Bogdanekevich and other 
officials. The meeting might be attended by Russian Prime 
Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin. 

