<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minsk, Moscow Reassure IMF Over Monetary Union </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201100694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0005 
GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1201100694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By unidentified BELINFORM correspondent for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Minsk, 12 Jan -- The signing of a statement by the 
Governments of the Russian Federation and Belarus on the 
forthcoming unification of their monetary systems should not 
have any effect on the results of cooperation between the 
republics and international financial organizations, a BELINFORM 
correspondent was told by Yevgeniy Bogomazov, head of the sector 
of the Belarusian Council of Ministers for coordinating the work 
of republican bodies with international economic and financial 
credit organizations. 
  He said that plenipotentiary representatives of the two 
republics had signed a message in Moscow to the IMF, the EBRD 
[European Bank for Reconstruction and Development] and other 
international organizations, in which they gave an assurance 
that the unification of the two monetary systems would not have 
an effect on the prospects for cooperation between the two 
republics and these organizations and would not affect the 
independent status of each of the republics. 

</TEXT>

