<H3> <TI>   New Train To Run Between Moscow, St. Petersburg </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1201093594 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 11 Jan 94 First 
Edition p 8 </F>

<F P=103> PM1201093594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Yevgeniy Solomenko: "Swift `Falcon' Will Bring </F>
Moscow and St. Petersburg Closer"] 
  [Text] St. Petersburg--The "Rubin" marine technology 
central design bureau has completed the development of the 
"Falcon" ["Sokol"] super-high-speed train. 
  This express train, which can cover 350 km in one hour, will 
run between St. Petersburg and Moscow. The plan has been handed 
over to the "Vysokoskorostnyye magistrali" Russian joint-stock 
company. 
  The superexpress is "Rubin's" first conversion venture. 
Until now the central design bureau has specialized in the 
creation of nuclear submarines and other warships. 

</TEXT>

