<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kuban Small Council To Seek Help From State Duma </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101160494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1357 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1101160494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Viktor Zhilyakov] </F>
  [Text] Krasnodar January 11 TASS -- A group of members of 
the Small Council of the Kuban intends to seek support from the 
State Duma and also to institute legal proceedings against 
governor of the territory, Nikolay Yegorov. Yegorov had signed a 
decree terminating as of this Tuesday the powers of The 
Territorial Council of People's Deputies. The apparatus of the 
council is dissolved. Elections to the Krasnodar territory are 
to be held on April 3. Until the beginning of the work of the 
future parliament, matters in the competence of the Territorial 
Council are to be decided by the head of the territorial 
administration. 

</TEXT>

