<F P=102>  LD1101190694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1704 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1101190694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Kokukhin] </F>
  [Text] Ioshkar Ola, January 11 (TASS) -- The youngest 
lawmaker was elected the speaker of the parliament of the 
Republic of Mari El in central European Russia. 
  Anatoliy Smirnov, who has not yet turned 30, defeated former 
speaker Yuriy Manakov who boasts the highest popularity rating 
in the republic, according to the latest opinion polls. 
  Smirnov made a typical Soviet-Russian style career. He began 
as an ordinary worker, but then switched to Komsomol, the youth 
branch of the former Soviet Communist Party, and succeeded to 
raise to the post of the secretary of a district party committee. 
  However, when market reforms began in the country, Smirnov 
abandoned the Communist post and went to work in a commercial 
bank and after that to a property managing fund which organised 
privatisation. 

</TEXT>

