<H3> <TI>   Missiles Fired at Russian Border Guard Post </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201094994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0906 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1201094994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Gridneva] </F>
  [Text] Dushanbe January 12 TASS -- Missile fire was again 
opened from the territory of Afghanistan Tuesday on the 12th 
post of the Moskovskiy detachment, guarding the Tajik frontier. 
ITAR-TASS has learned from military sources in Dushanbe that 
there were no casualties among Russian servicemen. 
  According to the same sources, the number of armed 
provocations on some sectors of the Tajik-Afghan border has 
increased sharply since early January. For instance, fire was 
opened on the deployment area of the 13th post of the Moskovskiy 
border guard detachment on Sunday. Tajik mujaheds fired eight 
shells at the post from Afghan territory. 
  Borderguards of the Pyanj detachment have cut short three 
attempts of small groups of Tajik opposition fighters to break 
into Tajikistan from Afghan territory in the past five days. 

