<H3> <TI>   Kazakhstan President Nazarbayev Continues Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Presidents Against Dual Citizenship </H4>
<F P=102> LD1101161494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1202 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1101161494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The presidents of Kazakhstan and Uzbekistan, 
Nursultan Nazarbayev and Islam Karimov, have spoken out against 
the idea of dual citizenship, which was introduced recently by 
Turkmenistan, they told reporters in Tashkent Monday. 
  Karimov, for example, has said that Russians living in 
Uzbekistan should believe that the republic's constitution 
provides them equal conditions and rights alongside the local 
population and other nations living in the republics. 
  For his part, Nazarbayev said that Kazakhstan's Constitution 
does not offer dual citizenship and he, as the president, must 
obey it. 

</TEXT>

