<H3> <TI>   Laar, Latvian Government Consult on Events in Riga </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101173994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1513 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1101173994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Estonian government's press service announced 
that during the night of January 10, Estonian President Mart 
Laar held telephone discussions with members of the Latvian 
government following a provocation in Riga against Russian 
servicemen and diplomats, and the placing of Russian troops in 
Latvia in a state of increased combat readiness. 
  The Latvian side informed Laar that the situation was 
getting 
back to normal. 
  Both sides compared the events with the situation in Latvia 
in 1940 which led to those countries' occupation by the Soviet 
Union, and emphasized the importance of preserving peace and 
stability, and of efforts to ensure their countries' security. 
  An agreement was reached on maintaining permanent contacts 
between the Latvian and Estonian governments until the crisis is 
resolved. 

</TEXT>

