<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Low-Educated Estonians Said To Favor Old Border </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0701131594 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 6 Jan 94 First 
Edition p 4 </F>

<F P=103> PM0701131594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Leonid Levitskiy: "Majority of Estonians in </F>
Favor of Review of Border with Russia"] 
  [Text] Tallinn -- The majority of Estonians consider that 
the border should be restored to its prewar position. 
  Estonia should get back Ivangorod, the area around the Narva 
river, and Pechory. But the majority of Estonians hope that a 
solution will be found which is acceptable to both states. The 
newspaper POSTIMEES drew this conclusion on the basis of a 
sociological poll carried out by the "Emor" company. 
Specialists questioned 1,000 people. These were on the whole 
young Estonians (16-24 years of age) and elderly Estonians 
(65-74 years of age), who stated that it is necessary to 
reinstate the Tartu (Yuryev) Peace Agreement and the border 
between the countries which it established. According to the 
paper, those with a low level of education favor the prewar 
border. Estonians with higher education and Estonians living in 
the republic's northeast come out in favor of a compromise 
solution for the border problem. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

