<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Meets With Belarus' Shushkevich; Treaty Discussed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201114794 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1100 GMT 
12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1201114794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At the meeting between Russian President Boris 
Nikolayevich Yeltsin and Stanislav Shushkevich, chairman of the 
Supreme Soviet of Belarus, in Moscow today, a detailed analysis 
was made of the interstate relations which have taken shape. 
  In the center of attention were questions of economic 
cooperation. There was also discussion of other questions of 
bilateral relations. The sides are convinced of the need to 
draft a new interstate Russian-Belarusian treaty of friendship 
and cooperation that highlights the desire of Russia and Belarus 
to build democratic states with a socially-oriented market 
economy and that also highlights the special level of economic, 
political, and human relations whicha are historical between the 
two countries. 

</TEXT>

