<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Communique on Treaty </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201123294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1131 
GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1201123294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 12 Jan (ITAR-TASS) -- At their meeting 
today, Russian President Boris Yeltsin and Stanislav 
Shushkevich, chairman of the Belarus Supreme Soviet came to the 
conviction that it is necessary to draw up a new interstate 
Russian-Belarus treaty on friendship and cooperation, which 
would be in line with Russia's and Belarus' desire to build 
democratic states with a socially-oriented market economy, and 
with the historically special level of economic, political, and 
human relations between the two countries. This message is 
contained in the communique released by the Russian president's 
press service. 
  A thorough analysis of the existing interstate relations was 
conducted at the meeting. Issues of economic cooperation were 
the focus of attention. Other questions of bilateral relations 
were also discussed, the document notes. 
  The two sides have exchanged opinions in connection with the 
forthcoming visits to Moscow and Minsk by U.S. President Bill 
Clinton, the communique notes. It has been noted that in the 
process of building economic relations with the United States, 
it is time to go from aid programs to programs of assistance in 
trade and investments as the main proviso of economic 
development and market integration of CIS countries' economies 
in the world economy. 

</TEXT>

