<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kostikov Warns Against Repeat of Incident </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201031094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1656 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1201031094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The spokesman for the Russian President Vyacheslav 
Kostikov has said Tuesday that Russia will take into account the 
American experience while responding to incidents like the one 
that happened with Russian military and diplomats in Riga 
January 10. 
  Latvian volunteers blocked several buildings belonging to 
the 
Russian army and kept two Russian generals in handcuffs for 
several hours and showed a disgusting approach to the Russian 
Ambassador in Latvia. 
  Russian Defense Minister Pavel Grachev has ordered that the 
Russian military transport planes, paratroopers and pilots in 
the republic be put to combat alert owing to the events in the 
Latvian capital. 
  Kostikov has told reporters in Moscow Tuesday that should 
similar incidents repeat, the reaction of the president and 
Russia would be tougher, I would say very tough taking into 
account the world precedents. 

</TEXT>

