<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Says Mitterrand `Senile' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK1201110094 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 12 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> MK1201110094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SEGODNYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [SEGODNYA report: "Zhirinovskiy Continues To Remove </F>
Presidents"] 
  [Text] Talking to journalists in the Duma lobby, Mr. 
Zhirinovskiy, leader of the Liberal Democratic Party of Russia, 
who is known to be actively pressing to be elected to the 
position of chairman of the parliament's foreign affairs 
committee, suddenly turned to international subjects. He 
described as "absolute fascism" the joint French-British 
initiative on a forcible settlement of the conflict in former 
Yugoslavia. He thus spoke about one of its authors, the French 
president: "That Mitterrand of yours has grown senile. He will 
last another half a year; so near his end, he dreams up all 
sorts of little ideas." 
  The reaction by President Mitterrand and the French Foreign 
Ministry to this statement is yet unknown. 

</TEXT>

