<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Naval Maneuvers With Kuwait Had `Anti-Iraqi Complexion' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1101141794 Moscow PRAVDA in Russian 11 Jan 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> PM1101141794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow PRAVDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Vladimir Belyakov report: "All Eggs in One Basket"] </F>
  [Text] Cairo, 10 Jan -- Evaluating the recently ended 
10-day joint Kuwaiti-Russian naval maneuvers held within the 
framework of the agreement on military cooperation between the 
two countries signed in Moscow at the end of November, a 
spokesman for the Kuwaiti Ministry of Defense described them as 
"excellent." 
  It would be possible to welcome Russia's contribution to 
ensuring Kuwait's security. But there is the troubling fact 
that Russian-Kuwaiti military cooperation has begun before the 
normalization of relations between Kuwait and Iraq and so 
inevitably acquires an anti-Iraqi complexion. The door to 
cooperation with Iraq -- a rich and influential state with which 
we used to be linked by very close ties -- has thereby 
essentially been slammed shut. In such a situation it is hardly 
rational, as our new friends, the Americans, say, to put all our 
eggs in one basket. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

