<H3> <TI>   Massive Azeri Losses Alleged </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1101204694 Yerevan SNARK in English 1342 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1101204694 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Stepanakert, January 11 (SNARK) -- In the short 
hours of quietness the Karabakh soldiers are busy with burying 
numerous bodies of the Azerbaijani militaries. It can be 
explained by the absence of the Azerbaijani leaders' desire to 
take the bodies of the soldiers and officers to conceal the true 
quantity of losses they have in the clashes. 
  According to the data received from the Staff of the 
Karabakh 
Defense Army, the great number unburied bodies -- about 350 -- 
are at the suburbs of the Madagiz village, Mardakertskiy region. 
During the period of last 20 days about 800 soldiers and 
officers of the Azerbaijani Army were killed there. They were 
the 18-19 years old, the residents of Baku and Sumgait. 
  Recently at the border of the Martuninskiy (Karabakh) and 
Agdamskiy (Azerbaijan) regions more than 200 lost Azeris 
militaries were buried in the common tomb. Their documents 
witness the fact -- they were within the Mingechaur infantry 
battalion. 

</TEXT>

