<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Says Azeris Reject Peaceful Solutions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101192894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1651 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1101192894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Presidential Bulletin" feature] </F>
  [Text] Azerbaijan still rejects all programmes of the 
peaceful solution of the Karabakh problem. More than that, in 
the past days it provokes military actions on the Armenian-Azeri 
border. Northern areas of Armenia were shelled in the most 
barbarous way, the presidential spokesman Aram Abramyan has told 
the briefing in Yerevan. 
  He has said Azerbaijan has again illusions to solve the 
problem militarily. Armenia's position is unchanged, the 
problem cannot be solved militarily, said Abramyan. That is why 
the Armenian leadership will use every possibility to try to 
solve the problem politically, said the spokesman. 
  In this connection he said that Armenia backs any 
peace-keeping initiative in this direction, including the recent 
initiative proposed by Iran. Out of its two key provisions -- 
the ceasefire and the status of Nagoro-Karabakh -- Armenia has 
concentrated on the first one, since only during the ceasefire 
it is possible to conduct talks on a political status. 

</TEXT>

