<H3> <TI>   Large Section of Gas Pipeline Blown Up </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1101210594 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1800 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1101210594 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1800 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] While the Armenian workers were 
repairing the blown up sectors of the pipeline in Marneulskiy 
Rayon, yet another explosion took place on Georgian territory. 
It surpasses the others in its magnitude. A 300-meter sector 
of the 1,000-mm gas pipeline was blown up and put out of order 
at the place where it crosses the Kura River in 
Azerbaijani-inhabited Gardabanskiy Rayon. Moreover, a 
800-meter-long sector of the pipeline was displaced by some 5 
meters. 
  Specialists from the Armenian State Gas Enterprise have left 
for the site of the accident. In their opinion, the Kura River 
should be diverted and large-scale earth moving should be 
carried out at the location of the explosion in order to be able 
to repair the pipeline. 

</TEXT>

