<H3> <TI>   Little Hope of Natural Gas Deliveries Soon </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1101201594 Yerevan SNARK in English 1402 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1101201594 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, January, 11 (SNARK) -- There are no hopes 
of receiving gas in the nearest future in Armenia, Roland 
Adonts, the General Director of the " Armenian Gas Industry " 
enterprise, has declared today to SNARK. 
  He said the Georgian Government is helpless and incapable 
not 
only to provide with the security of the pipeline but also to 
cope with the Azerbaijani military joints [as received] acting 
in that part of Georgia. 
  Adonts declared that Azerbaijani militants control all the 
elevations along the Southern part of the pipeline. He said it 
hampers the reconstruction of the pipeline. In the same time 
Roland Adonts rejected the idea of Armenia's military 
interference for provision of the pipeline security. He 
considers it impossible because this region of Georgia is 
basically inhabited by Azerbaijanians. This problem requires a 
serious political and military interference of Russia and 
Georgia. 

