<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Karabakh Front Offensive Launched </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101180894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1635 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1101180894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vadim Byrkin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 11 TASS -- After a relatively calm 
night, the Azeri National Army resumed offensive operations at 
many sections of the Karabakh front, sources at the Karabakh 
defence army headquarters' press center told ITAR-TASS. 
  The fighting was especially fierce in the Karabakh Mardakert 
region on the line of Madagis-Akop Kamari settlements and on the 
border of the Agdam region. All the attacks were repulsed by 3 
P.M. 
  After a counter-offensive, Karabakh units seized a number of 
heights in the Mardakert region. 

</TEXT>

