<H3> <TI>   Russians Said Forced Into Army </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101175494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1645 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1101175494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to the military and radio intelligence of 
the Nagorno-Karabakh army, Azerbaijanis send units composed 
mostly of citizens of various CIS states as well as Turkey and 
Afghanistan to the areas of the fiercest fighting. 
  A resident of the Russian city of Vladivostok, now 
prisoner-of-war Oleg Pilipenko, said that the Azerbaijani 
authorities arrest Russians who temporarily reside on the 
territory of Azerbaijan and force them into enrolling to the 
Azerbaijani army by beating. 
  According to sources in Stepanakert, Pilipenko recently 
appealed to the Russian authorities to help him and other 
Russians who were made to serve in the Azerbaijani army. 
  Another POW, resident of the Turkish town of Sivac Abil 
Umah, 
stated that a group of officers of the Azerbaijani Defense 
Ministry was touring Turkey at the moment drafting Turkish 
jobless into the national army. 
  Meanwhile, Azerbaijani President Geydar Aliyev recently said 
Baku had irrefutable evidence of mercenaries' participation in 
the Armenian-Azerbaijani conflict on the Armenian side. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

