<H3> <TI>   Aliyev Pardon of Biregadi Battalion Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1101173694 Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network in Azeri 1600 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1101173694 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Azeri </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Text" of President Geydar Aliyev's amnesty decree for the </F>
Biregadi Battalion on 10 January -- read by announcer] 
  [Text] Considering the fact that the Biregadi Battalion's 
fighters have admitted their criminal offense and said that they 
repent what they have done and are ready to try to rectify their 
mistake by going to the front lines to bravely fight against the 
enemy, and acting in the light of humanitarian principles and 
Azerbaijan's Constitution, I have decided: 
  That the Biregadi Battalion's military personnel, who have 
been convicted of committing a criminal offense, be pardoned and 
released from prison to be sent to join the fighting army units 
under the defense minister's orders. 
  [Signed] President Geydar Aliyev 
  [Dated] Baku City, 10 January 1994 

