<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aliyev Issues Decree To Aid Foreign Trade </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1101174394 Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network in Azeri 1600 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1101174394 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Azeri </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Geydar Aliyev has signed a decree on the 
measures to be taken to promote foreign trade in the republic. 
The decree stresses that the republic's state establishments 
and organizations can sell commodities or provide services to 
foreign countries within the framework of their foreign trade 
relations only on the basis of letters of credit or advance 
payments until the legal formalities are concluded. In 
addition, advance payment of dues for commodities and services 
from foreign countries is banned. Imports of foreign products 
and services by foreign countries will be paid through letters 
of credit. 
  The decree says that registering barter trade transactions 
has been deemed appropriate. Meanwhile, it approves the new 
list of the strategically important items for the republic, 
reducing their number of 17. 
  The full text of the decree and the list of the 
strategically 
important items, which has been drawn up with the president's 
consent, will be published in the press. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

