<H3> <TI>   Subscriptions to Russian Newspaper in Jeopardy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1101141994 Moscow PRAVDA in Russian 11 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM1101141994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow PRAVDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Zaur Kadymbekov report: "Will PRAVDA Reach Baku?"] </F>
  [Text] Baku -- Confusion over mutual transactions, the 
lack of a sufficient number of Russian rubles in Azerbaijan, and 
the impossibility of money transfers to Russia have introduced 
complete chaos into financial relations between the two 
countries -- which has not been slow to affect subscriptions to 
Russian publications, their delivery, and their printing in the 
republic. 
  Meanwhile, according to the information of the local 
Ministry 
of Communications, subscriptions to them have been taken out in 
Azerbaijan to the value of 150 million rubles. Citing the same 
old reasons, the leadership of the national bank has proposed 
returning the money to the subscribers. But Nazim Novruzov, 
chief of the Azerbaijani Press Distribution Association, has 
declared that possibilities have nonetheless been found to 
preserve four Russian newspapers for the readers: PRAVDA, 
IZVESTIYA, KOMSOMOLSKAYA PRAVDA, and ARGUMENTY I FAKTY. 

</TEXT>

