<H3> <TI>   Shumeyko To Quit Government Post If Elected Speaker </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101180294 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1700 GMT 
11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1101180294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Federation Council deputies today drew up a 
ballot paper for the election of the chairman of the upper 
chamber of parliament. [passage omitted] In order to be elected 
speaker of the Federation Council, it is necessary to receive 86 
votes, INTERFAX points out. 
  In an interview with that agency, Vladimir Shumeyko declared 
that, if elected, he will leave the post of first vice premier 
of the Russian Government. 
  According to Shumeyko, a decision will soon be adopted in 
the 
Federation Council according to which the leadership of the 
chamber, unlke ordinary deputies, will operate on a permanent 
basis. 

