<DOCNO> FBIS3-55881 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov008_c_94012" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-008 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  12 Jan 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Conflict Ensues Over Chairman of Duma Session </TI></H3>
<H4>   Replacement of Lukava Demanded </H4>
<F P=102> LD1101150694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1431 
GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1101150694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Aleksandrova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 11 Jan -- The atmosphere in the State Duma 
building deteriorated sharply today immediately on resumption of 
work after the daytime break over a conflict concerning the 
person in the chair. 
  A number of deputies immediately demanded that Georgiy 
Lukava, a deputy from the Liberal Democratic Party of Russia 
[LDPR], be replaced as chairman of the session as, in the view 
of many, his lack of experience meant he was not up to the task. 
In accordance with the Constitution, Georgiy Lukava opened the 
first session of the State Duma as the oldest of the deputies, 
and it was thought that he would chair the session until a 
speaker was elected. 
  Some deputies suggested that Georgiy Lukava should give up 
his place to one of the more competent deputies by means of a 
Duma resolution. However, Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, the LDPR 
leader, from a microphone in the hall, gave the stand-in 
chairman a categorical instruction "to go nowhere, switch off 
the microphone, and not allow anyone onto the podium." He 
demanded that discussion of the issue of the numbers in a 
faction be resumed, having been stopped before the break, and if 
necessary that "the militia be called." 
  The indignant deputies protested and refused to take part in 
the electronic registration announced by Georgiy Lukava. As a 
result, the electronic board showed that there was no quorum 
several times in a row. The first session of the State Duma 
continues -- for the time being -- in a less than constructive 
spirit. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-55882 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov008_c_94013" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-008 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  12 Jan 1994 </DATE1>

