<H3> <TI>   Shakhray: Speaker Needs 2 Deputies </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101191694 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1100 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1101191694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Sergey Shakhray, leader of the Russian Unity and 
Accord Party, believes that Russia's Choice refusal to 
participate in consultations of major factions has given 
deputies from one-seat constituencies a better chance to be 
included in the management bodies of the State Duma. 
  In an interview to INTERFAX, he said that the proposal to 
elect candidates to all management bodies of the chamber on a 
basis of a single list would have little support. Sergey 
Shakhray said that the media and independent deputies favor 
individual and secret voting for every candidate. 
  He believes that the parliamentary chairman should have only 
two deputies, one from the party list and the other from a 
one-seat constituency. 

</TEXT>

