<H3> <TI>   State Duma Takes Break, To Reconvene 13 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101164694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1623 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1101164694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Ivan Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 11 TASS -- The Russian State Duma has 
announced a day and a half break to convene again at 12:30 [0930 
GMT] on January 13. 
  The break was suggested by Deputy Sergey Shakhray, who said 
deputy factions, groups and their leaders need some time for 
organizational work in view of the upcoming elections of the 
State Duma speaker and his deputies, formation of the State Duma 
committees and election of their heads and adoption of the State 
Duma time-limit. 
  Deputies have agreed to hold their morning sessions from 10 
a.m. through 2 p.m. With a 30-minute break at noon and 
afternoon sessions from 4 p.m. through 6 p.m. 

</TEXT>

