<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ardzinba:`Vanquished Do Not Dictate Terms' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK1101140094 Moscow KURANTY in Russian 11 Jan 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> MK1101140094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KURANTY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Inga Agbarova: "Ardzinba Does Not See Any </F>
Prospects"] 
  [Text] "I do not see any prospects in the talks," 
Abkhazian leader Vladislav Ardzinba said on Gudauta radio 
referring to the upcoming second round of talks between Georgia 
and Abkhazia in Geneva. "The vanquished do not dictate terms to 
the victors," he said, "Hence, Tbilisi will have to put up with 
the fact that our relations must be based on agreements reached 
between equal subjects of international law. The Georgian side 
is constantly exploiting the problem of refugees. As for us, we 
do not prevent them from returning to their home country." 
Well-informed sources at the Georgian Foreign Ministry believe 
that such statements made on the eve of the upcoming 
Georgian-Abkhazian consultations scheduled for 11 January are 
provocative and may bring about the most undesirable 
consequences. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

