<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Money Changers Stop Dealing in Georgian Coupons </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1101220594 Yerevan SNARK in English 1550 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1101220594 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi, January 11 (SNARK) -- Today the private 
exchange offices stopped the operations of exchanging of Russian 
rubles for Georgian currency because coupons dropped down. The 
high-price goods disappeared from the shops. 
  At the last auction of Interbanking Exchange of National 
Bank 
of Georgia there was the rate -- 100 Georgian coupons for 1 
Russian ruble. Comparing with the previous auction the rate is 
dropped down 20 points. Specialists connect the collapsing 
dropping down of coupons with the recent statement of Vakhtang 
Goguadze, the speaker of Georgian Parliament, about necessity of 
Georgia's entering to the ruble zone. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

