<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Russian Proposal on Skrunda </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101184194 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1800 GMT 11 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1101184194 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At the Latvian-Russian talks on army withdrawal, 
representatives of the Russian delegation have submitted new 
proposals on the legal status of the Skrunda radar station as 
well as a proposed new five-year deadline for the withdrawal of 
the Skrunda radar. This was told today to reporters by Sergey 
Zotov, head of the Russian delegation. 
  The Latvian side is at the moment acquainting itself with 
the 
new Russian proposals. The Latvian delegation believes that the 
facility should be non-military. Russian representatives, 
however, oppose that. 
  Speaking about the resumption of the talks in general after 
yesterday's incident between the leadership of the Vidzeme 
district of Riga and two generals of the Russian army, Zotov 
explained that one of the aims of the person responsible for the 
provocation was to disrupt the talks and to hinder the effort to 
reach agreement between Latvia and Russia on troop withdrawal. 
With this, suspension of the talks would have been only in the 
interest of the person responsible for the provocation. 
  The talks between representatives of the Latvian and Russian 
delegations on troop withdrawal will continue tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

