<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prosecutor: Reasons `Not Very Clear' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK1201091694 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 12 Jan 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> MK1201091694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [POSTFACTUM report under the "In Brief" rubric: "A Version </F>
of the `Latvian' Incident"] 
  [Text] Jazep Antsan, deputy general prosecutor of Latvia, 
has told a number of Moscow correspondents over the telephone 
that reasons for the attempted seizure of the complex of 
buildings by the local authorities from the Russian Army are not 
very clear. According to the prosecutor, the building that was 
the site of illegal actions by Latvian executive committee 
guards was a cultural center comprising a costly hotel, swimming 
pool, and sports facilities. The greater part of this complex 
is rented out to representatives of local commercial 
organizations of Latvia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

