<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Immediate Preparation' Ordered </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1101203294 Tallinn BNS in English 1746 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1101203294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Brussels, Jan 11, BNS - Lithuanian moved 
Tuesday towards accepting NATO's offer of a "Partnership for 
Peace," taking a lead among former Soviet states. 
  President Algirdas Brazauskas instructed his government to 
start "immediate preparation" to sign a partnership document 
with the Western alliance. 
  In a statement distributed by the Lithuanian embassy in 
Brussels, Brazauskas said partnership "paves the way to the full 
integration of Lithuania into the NATO political-military 
structures." [passage omitted] 
  Brazauskas said the Baltic republic, which borders Russia, 
would identify "facilities, resources and forces," that could be 
used in the partnership. 

</TEXT>

