<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Presidential Advisor Comments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201101694 Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network in Lithuanian 
0900 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1201101694 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Lithuanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Interfax Baltic News Service reports that Justas 
Paleckis, the Lithuanian president's foreign policy adviser, 
told an INTERFAX correspondent that the decisions made by the 
NATO summit in Brussels on cooperation of this organization with 
Central and East European countries met the expectations of 
realistically thinking politicians. 
  According to him, following the approval in Brussels of the 
Partnership for Peace NATO program, the rapprochement of 
Lithuania with this organization would depend on the opening 
possibilities: political stability, the economic potential of 
Lithuania, the ability to organize and improve military 
structures according to European standards, and the ability to 
cooperate both with NATO and other Baltic states. 
  Justas Paleckis thinks that a strong incentive to start 
implementing the Partnership for Peace NATO program will be the 
visit to Brussels by Lithuanian President Algirdas Brazauskas, 
due to take place on 27 January. 
  According to the president's adviser, the main objective of 
the visit to Brussels will be to convince NATO leadership that 
Lithuania's commitment to rapprochement with NATO is not 
directed against Russia or other neighboring states. 

</TEXT>

