<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Former Minister Reacts </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1201112194 Tallinn BNS in English 0708 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1201112194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius, Jan 11, BNS -- The Lithuanian Ministry of 
Defense purchased all weapons in accordance with respective 
government resolutions, which provide for "specific mediators, 
prices, and terms of payment," former Defense Minister Audrius 
Butkevicius said in a written statement Friday [7 January]. 
  Recent publications about the Ministry of Defense in the 
RESPUBLIKA newspaper are "irresponsible, biassed and aimed at 
creating sensational news at any cost," the ex-minister said. 
  Butkevicius said he regrets that the timing of a series of 
articles in RESPUBLIKA "coincided with Lithuania's statement on 
its intention to approach West European defensive structures." 
  The former minister said Lithuania had to choose from two 
ways of behaving before it was internationally recognized -- 
either to carry out a policy of doing nothing, or to develop 
national defense. "I and my colleagues chose the second way." 

</TEXT>

