<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Reports Illegal Transit of Russians </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1201095394 Vilnius RESPUBLIKA in Lithuanian 30 Dec 93 No. 
252 p 3 </F>

<F P=103> WS1201095394 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius RESPUBLIKA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Lithuanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Gytis Vaidila: "Transit Without Permit"] </F>
  [Text] As the National Defense Ministry has reported, at 
2155 [1955 GMT] on 28 December, 101 Russian Fleet seamen, two 
warrant officers, and one third rank captain crossed the border 
check point in Turmantas [Lithuanian border crossing with 
Latvia] without a transit permit on a passenger train heading 
from Kaliningrad to St. Petersburg. This train stood for half 
an hour in Kybartai [Lithuanian border crossing with Kaliningrad 
Oblast]. According to the chief of the shift on duty there, 
border guards did not have enough time to check the entire 
train, and the Russian servicemen might have slipped across the 
border in this way. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

