<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Emergency Committee Redesignated as Ministry </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101194694 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1700 GMT 
11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1101194694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In accordance with the decree "On the structure of 
the federal bodies of executive authority," signed by the 
Russian president, the Russian State Committee for Emergency 
Situations has been redesignated as a ministry. This has been 
reported by ITAR- TASS. 
  According to the new structure of the federal bodies of 
executive authority, that department is assigned to the block of 
power ministries. 
  The former committee's press service has said that from 
today 
the functions of the abolished committee for the social support 
of citizens and the rehabilitation of territories that have 
suffered from Chernobyl and other radiation catastrophes have 
been transferred to the new ministry, as well as the functions 
of the committee for carrying out special-purpose under-water 
work. Also transferred to the ministry as a state institution 
is the Russian Federal Aerospace Search and Rescue Service. 

</TEXT>

