<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Directive on Cadre Policy Council Task </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1101133394 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 11 Jan 94 
p 5 </F>

<F P=103> PM1101133394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Directive No. 792-rp of the Russian Federation President, </F>
signed by Russian Federation President B. Yeltsin, dated 31 
December 1993] 
  [Text] In accordance with the Statute on the Council for 
Cadre Policy Under the President of the Russian Federation, 
ratified by edict No. 848 of the president of the Russian 
Federation dated 3 June 1993: 
  1. The Council for Cadre Policy Under the President of the 
Russian Federation is charged with overal coordination of the 
work to prepare draft acts of the president of the Russian 
Federation, whose adoption is necessitated by the Statute on the 
Federal State Service, ratified by edict No. 2267 of the 
president of the Russian Federation dated 22 December 1993. 
  2. V.F. Shumeyko and S.A. Filatov, cochairmen of the Council 
for Cadre Policy Under the President of the Russian Federation, 
are to submit for ratification within 10 days a work schedule 
for the preparation of draft acts indicated in Point 1 of this 
directive. 
  [Signed] President of the Russian Federation B. Yeltsin 
  [Dated] 31 December 1993 

