<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Criminal Proceedings Against Lukyanov To Continue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201115494 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1000 GMT 
12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1201115494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] There are no legal grounds for discontinuing 
criminal proceedings against Anatoliy Lukyanov and Vasiliy 
Starodubtsev, who have both been elected to the Russian Federal 
Assembly. This ruling was made today by the court of the 
Supreme Court Military Board, which is in charge of the case of 
the State Committee for the State of Emergency [SCSE]. 
  Lukyanov's lawyer, Genrikh Padva, applied for the criminal 
proceedings against his client and Vasiliy Starodubtsev to be 
discontinued pending the adoption of the law on the status of 
deputies. 
  In the court's opinion, the adoption of the law will not 
free 
the defendants from criminal liability. Nor does the Russian 
Constitution, adopted at the 12 December referendum, free the 
SCSE trial defendants from liability, the court believes. 
  INTERFAX reports that the trial is to be resumed at 0900 on 
13 January. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

