<H3> <TI>   Economic Security Commission Session Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK1101144094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 11 Jan 94 
p 2 </F>

<F P=103> MK1101144094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [RIA untitled report under the "In Brief" rubric] </F>
  [Text] Moscow -- The first session of the Russian 
Federation Security Council's interdepartmental commission on 
economic security took place in Moscow yesterday. Andrey 
Zverev, head of the economic department of the Russian 
Federation Government staff, was appointed chairman of the 
commission by a decree of Russian President Boris Yeltsin. The 
session also examined questions connected with the elaboration 
of an economic security state doctrine, and the progress of 
economic reform in the country among other problems. Taking 
part in the session were the heads of ministries and agencies 
represented on the commission. 

</TEXT>

