<H3> <TI>   Labor Commission To Consider `General Agreement' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1101173394 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 11 Jan 94 
First Edition p 2 </F>

<F P=103> PM1101173394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Aleksandr Golyayev : "Trilateral Commission </F>
Begins..."] 
  [Text] The Russian Trilateral Commission on Regulating 
Social and Labor Relations is resuming its work. Next Wednesday 
representatives of the government, Russian trade unions, and the 
country's entrepreneurs will gather at the Russian Federation 
Ministry of Labor in order to discuss a candidate nominated for 
the post of coordinator. It is proposed that the draft of a 
future general agreement also be scrutinized. This question 
will be on the agenda of the conference of leaders of regional 
and sector committees of trade unions belonging to the 
Federation of Independent Trade Unions of Russia taking place at 
the end of the week in the Moscow area. 

</TEXT>

