<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Claims Armenians Fleeing Battlefield </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1101200794 Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network in Azeri 1600 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1101200794 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Azeri </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Azerbaijani Defense Ministry press service 
reports: Despite suffering considerable losses in men and 
material in recent days, Armenia's Army units are not giving up 
their unsuccessful attempts to attack Azerbaijani territory. 
  The enemy launched several futile attacks against our 
positions in Fizulinskiy and Terterskiy rayons through the day 
on 10 January and the morning of 11 January. Our troops bravely 
halted the attacks and inflicted crushing blows on the enemy. 
  According to information obtained from the occupied lands, 
the Armenian troops are abandoning their positions in panic and 
are fleeing toward Armenia. Clashes are taking place between 
those fleeing in disarray and fighters coming from Armenia. It 
appears that Armenia's military command has been left with no 
choice but to institute punishment measures to prevent the mass 
desertions. 

</TEXT>

