<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Baltic Presidents Praise Partnership for Peace Invitation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201145394 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1400 GMT 12 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1201145394 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Estonian President Lennart Meri, Latvian 
President Guntis Ulmanis, and Lithuanian President Algirdas 
Brazauskas have circulated a joint statement in which the 
invitation for the Baltic states to participate in the NATO 
program, Partnership for Peace, is valued positively. 
  The statement stresses that the program offers concrete 
possibilities for the development of cooperation between NATO 
and the Baltic states. The presidents also express hope that 
the armed forces of the Baltic states would be transformed so 
that they would be able to cooperate with NATO. 
  [Second announcer] The statement also says that the task to 
secure the status of a member state will not be easy, and it 
should be carried out by all the East European states together. 
In addition, mutual trust and cooperation on the whole 
continent and in the Baltic Sea region will strengthen in the 
framework of the Partnership for Peace program of cooperation 
between all European states. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

