<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vice President Holds Talks With Iranians </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1201214894 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1400 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1201214894 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1400 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Armenian Vice President Gagik Arutyunyan left 
for Zangezur [southern Armenia] where an extraordinary session 
of the state commission coordinating Armenian-Iranian ties is 
being held. 
  Armenian presidential press service reported that Gagik 
Arutyunyan, accompanied by the rayon leadership, held a meeting 
with the directors of the enterprises in Megrinskiy Rayon. They 
examined matters pertaining to the development of the 
Armenian-Iranian economic ties. 
  After that, a session of the state commission coordinating 
Armenian-Iranian ties was held in Megri. Morteza Bank, head of 
the Eastern Europe and CIS Department at the Iranian Foreign 
Ministry, and Ahmad Sobhani, the Iranian charge d'affaires in 
Armenia, took part on the Iranian side. 
  The meeting discussed matters relating to the construction 
of 
the bridge over Araks River, and the regulation of 
communications, border trade, and customs procedures, including 
the coordination of the work of the customs departments of the 
two countries. 
  Morteza Bank stressed in particular that Iran has 
considerable experience in organizing border trade and it could 
substantially contribute to the organization of similar trade 
with Armenia. He was also positively disposed to Armenian 
side's proposal to open an Armenian mission in Tabriz. 
  The sides agreed to organize such meetings frequently. Vice 
President Gagik Arutyunyan stressed that this would speed up the 
work to develop the bilateral ties. 
  Gagik Arutyunyan also held a separate meeting with Morteza 
Bank and Ahmad Sobhani. 

</TEXT>

