<H3> <TI>   Parliament Approves Privatization Program </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1201200494 Yerevan SNARK in English 1336 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1201200494 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, January 12 (SNARK) -- Today the Armenian 
Parliament accepted the 1994 privatization program suggested by 
the Armenian Government. There will be privatized the units of 
the uncompleted construction, agriculture, trade and public 
service. 
  Speaking to the extraordinary session of the Armenian 
Parliament the Armenian President Levon Ter-Petrosyan accepted 
the fact that the Republic is essentially behind of the 
privatization process. "Armenia did only two serious `steps' in 
privatization -- there were privatized only flats and land", 
Levon Ter-Petrosyan declared. 
  According to Levon Ter-Petrosyan, "the expected 1994 
privatization of the state enterprises won't influence the 
Armenian economy because of the small volumes". 

</TEXT>

