<H3> <TI>   Names Asaturyan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1201203594 Yerevan SNARK in English 1527 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1201203594 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, January 12 (SNARK) -- One of the active 
figures of the party at power, that is Armenian National 
[Pannational] Movement, Bagrat Asaturyan was elected as a new 
Chairman of the Central Bank of Armenia. Earlier he headed a 
parliamentary commission on social aspects and health care. A 
38-year-old economist, graduate of the Yerevan Institute of 
National Economy, worked at the Institute of Economy of the 
National Academy of Sciences for a long period of time, defended 
a thesis for a candidate decree. President Levon Ter-Petrosyan 
who submitted the candidature of a new head of the Central Bank 
informed at the parliament session that Asaturyan "took an 
active part in arrangements concerning money exchange in 
Nagorno-Karabakh at the end of the last year". 
  Armen Darbinyan, the former Head of the ''Armenintorg'' 
enterprise, was elected as the first deputy of the Head of the 
Central Bank of Armenia. 

</TEXT>

