<H3> <TI>   Law Affects Currency Violation Regulations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1101220194 Yerevan SNARK in English 1550 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1101220194 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Joint Statement of the Ministry of Finance and Central </F>
Bank of Armenia"] 
  [Text] Yerevan, January 11 (SNARK) -- The juridical and 
natural persons on the territory of Armenia, who use foreign 
currency, including Russian rubles, for paying operations and 
haven't the license of the Central Bank of Armenia, will be 
prosecuted and may condemn to three-year imprisonment. 
Press-Center of the Central Bank informs SNARK about it. 
  Simultaneously it is said in the statement on the territory 
of Armenia the legal means for paying are the notes of the State 
Bank of the USSR of 1961-1992 with value till 500 rubles and 
Armenian drams of 1993 with value 10, 25, 50, 100, 200, 500 
drams. 

</TEXT>

