<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Losses Claim Refuted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201155994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1433 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1201155994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Karabakh troops killed 46 Azerbaijani soldiers on 
Tuesday after it surrounded an Azerbaijani unit in the Mardakert 
region, northern Karabakh. 
  A spokesman for the Army of the self-proclaimed 
Nagorno-Karabakh Republic has told Interfax that yet another 270 
Azerbaijani servicemen have been put out of action on other 
fronts. 
  Meanwhile, Karabakh has regained control over a number of 
strategic heights, earlier captured by Azerbaijan. 
  The Karabakh Army's casualties on Tuesday were estimated at 
6 
killed and 15 wounded. 
  By latest reports from Stepanakert, Azerbaijani troops 
mounted an offensive virtually on all fronts on Wednesday. 
Bitter fighting is under way. 
  Meanwhile, Azerbaijan's Defence Ministry has refuted as 
false 
Armenia's reports about Azerbaijan's heavy casualties in the 
fighting. 
  It contended that last week's Azerbaijani losses in both man 
power and material were much smaller than Armenia's damage. 
  A ministry spokesman estimated Armenia's losses in the 
Mardakert region where Azerbaijani troops ringed two Karabakh 
battalions on Tuesday at 30 men and three tanks. 
  Yet another 35 Armenian soldiers reportedly lost their lives 
in fighting on the Askeran and Agdam fronts and in the Fizuli 
region, Azerbaijan. Several tanks and artillery guns were 
smashed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

