<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Azeri </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Defense Ministry press service reports the 
following for 12 January: 
  The Armenian military units tried to launch an offensive on 
11 January in the Hakop-Kamari [Lulasaz] sector of the front 
that lies towards Terter. The enemy, who launched three attacks 
during the day, suffered considerable losses in men and material 
and had to withdraw. 
  Our brave soldiers have brought to naught every Armenian 
offensive in Agdamskiy and Beylagan rayons. 
  The high command of the Armenian Armed Forces, whose attacks 
towards Beylagan and Terter were defeated, is now working to 
exacerbate the situation on our republic's northwestern borders. 
The settlements in our republic's Tauzskiy, Kazakhskiy, and 
Kedabekskiy rayons came under unceasing long-range artillery 
shelling at 1830 on 11 January from Armenia's Berd, 
Idzhevanskiy, and Krasnoselskiy rayons. Our army units took 
countermeasures to silence the ferocious enemy. 

