<H3> <TI>   UN, Swiss Humanitarian Assistance Noted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1101223694 Baku TURAN in English 1618 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1101223694 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku, January 11 (TURAN) -- A large amount of 
humanitarian assistance from Switzerland -- 240 thousand tons of 
wheat flour is to be delivered to Azerbaijan in the near future. 
On News Year's Eve, Azerbaijan received 580 tons of wheat 
flour from Switzerland. 
  The shipment of assistance from Switzerland to Azerbaijan 
has 
been going on since December 29, 1993. The UN World Food 
Program (UNWFP) organized the delivery of 27 tons of food 
parcels from Switzerland to Azerbaijan. Prior to that, 39 tons 
of food were delivered for Azerbaijani refugees and displaced 
persons by the UNWFP . 
  The United Nation's High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) 
and its Humanitarian Assistance Commission will begin the 
distribution of assistance following the delivery of the last 
lot. 
  In addition, TURAN NEWS AGENCY was told at the UNO [United 
Nations Orgaization] Office in Azerbaijan that 6 containers, 
each of which include 20 tons of food, arrived. These goods 
were given to Azerbaijan by the European Community. An 
additional 314 containers will be delivered to Azerbaijan under 
the aegis of the European Community Assistance Programme in the 
near future. 

</TEXT>

