<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Captain First Rank Valeriy Gromak: "Young </F>
Journalists Become Ministers"] 
  [Text] The Estonian president has appointed Juri Luik, the 
country's former defense minister, as foreign minister. His 
post has been taken by Indrek Kannik, hitherto an adviser to the 
foreign minister. Evidently Juri Luik will leave his post as 
head of delegation at the talks with Russia, since, according to 
the Estonian side, his new post will not allow him to conduct 
talks with "a mere ambassador of the Russian Federation." 
  Luik and Kannik are recent graduates from the Tartu 
University Journalism Faculty and members of the Estonian 
student community; they are 27 years old, and have not yet 
settled down to married life. 

</TEXT>

