<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Clinton Arrives in Moscow, Welcomed by Chernomyrdin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201230494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2228 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1201230494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Aleksandr Krylovich] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 13 TASS -- Russian Prime Minister 
Viktor Chernomyrdin welcomed U.S. President Bill Clinton who 
arrived in Moscow early on Thursday [13 January]. 
  The official welcoming ceremony with a guard of honour and 
national anthems was not held because of the late time of 
arrival. 
  From the airport Clinton's motorcade left for the "Radisson- 
Slavyanskaya" hotel where the U.S. President will be staying. 
It is a 30-minute drive from the airport to the hotel. 

</TEXT>

