<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin, Clinton Begin Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301074294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0732 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1301074294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Ivan Ivanov and Gennadiy </F>
Talalayev] 
  [Text] Moscow January 13 TASS--The Russian-American summit 
talks began in the Kremlin today in the morning immediately 
after the official greeting ceremony. 
  After the beginning of the talks both presidents expressed 
confidence that the dialogue between Russia and the U.S. would 
promote the consolidation of world peace and tranquility, as 
well as the deepening of cooperation between the two countries. 
  On the first stage the talks are held in a narrow format at 
the Green Hall of the Grand Kremlin Palace. Aside from Yeltsin 
and Clinton, they are attended by Dmitriy Ryurikov, assistant to 
the Russian president, and Strobe Talbott, special adviser to 
the U.S. secretary of state on the new independent states. 
  According to the information from reliable sources, during 
their first one-hour meeting the Russian and U.S. presidents are 
expected to discuss issues dealing with economic and political 
cooperation between the two countries, the implementation of the 
Russian reform, the consolidation of international security, 
specifically, the settlement of regional conflicts and the 
non-proliferation of nuclear weapons. Probably, they will touch 
upon the mechanism of putting into effect Ukraine's decision on 
the withdrawal of nuclear warheads from its territory. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

