<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev To Visit China `At the End of January' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201194794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1822 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1201194794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [by ITAR-TASS correspondent Georgiy Shmelev] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 12 TASS -- Russian Foreign Minister 
Andrey Kozyrev is scheduled to visit China at the end of 
January, according to Deputy Foreign Minister Aleksandr Panov. 
  In an interview with ITAR-TASS on Wednesday Panov underlined 
that, after the Russian president's historic "break-through" 
visit to Beijing, Russia is now engaging in a wide, dynamic 
range of cooperation with China both on the international scene 
and in their bilateral relations. Panov said China is a high 
priority in Russia's foreign policy. 
  The deputy minister reported that Kozyrev's visit will 
include preparations for a return visit to Moscow by the Chinese 
chairman. 
  Panov thinks that the fact that Russia's new year is 
beginning with visits by the American President to Moscow and 
then the Russian foreign minister to Beijing is symbolic. 
Although these delegations are in different "weight 
categories", the two visits will maintain equilibrium in 
Russia's foreign policy, which is directed to the east as much 
as it is to the west. 

</TEXT>

