<H4>   Comments on Latvian Situation </H4>
<F P=102> LD1201144894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1355 
GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1201144894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondents Aleksandr Krylovich </F>
and Vladimir Taranov] 
  [Text] Moscow, 12 Jan -- It is of fundamental importance 
that all the specific perpetrators of the unlawful, provocative, 
and unfriendly acts committed on 10 January by armed Latvian 
militia against the Russian ambassador and two Russian generals 
in Riga receive due punishment, Grigoriy Karasin, the director 
of the Russian Federation Foreign Affairs Ministry Information 
and Press Department, said today at a briefing at the Russian 
Federation Foreign Affairs Ministry Press Center 
  He stressed that it was also essential for the Latvian 
authorities to take every measure necessary to prevent such 
highly dangerous incidents occurring in future. 
  Grigoriy Karasin said that Moscow was awaiting a detailed 
official response by the Latvian side to Russia's actions. 

