<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Spokesman Briefs on Various Issues </TI></H3>
<H4>   Welcomes Israeli-PLO Talks </H4>
<F P=102> LD1201200694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1649 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1201200694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondents Aleksandr Krylovich </F>
and Vladimir Taranov] 
  [Text] Moscow January 12 TASS -- Russia welcomes the 
renewal of negotiations in Egypt between delegations from Israel 
and the Palestinian Liberation Organization. Russia is hoping 
for the successful outcome of the talks, which concern an 
agreement on the Gaza Strip and Jericho, according to Grigoriy 
Karasin, the director of the information and press department of 
the Russian Ministry of Foreign Affairs, speaking in the 
ministry's press centre. 
  Karasin expressed his regret about several interruptions in 
the Israeli-PLO talks on specific measures to implement their 
declaration on principles, signed in September of 1993. 
  "In our contacts with both Israeli and Palestinian 
representatives we always point out to them the necessity of 
concentrating maximum constructive effort and good will on 
overcoming differences and following the spirit and the letter 
of the September agreements", the Russian representative stated. 

</TEXT>

