<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   North Ossetian Official Views Federation Council </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1201192294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1310 
GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1201192294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikazkaz, 12 Jan -- "The Federation Council, 
consisting mainly of the leaders of executive organs of power in 
Russia's republics, krays, and oblasts, must learn from the sad 
experience of the working of the former Russian Congress of 
People's Deputies and prevent confrontation with the president's 
staff and the government," an ITAR-TASS correspondent was told 
today by Akhsarbek Galazov, head of the Republic of North 
Ossetia, on his return from the first sitting in Moscow of 
Russia's new parliament. 
  Galazov thinks that the Federation Council will accomplish 
its historic role if it resolves the artificially created 
problems associated with the confrontation of the regions. "It 
is the republics that form the basis for Russian federalism and 
reducing them to the level of the other components of Russia may 
lead to an intensification of separatist sentiment and the 
disintegration of the Russian Federation," the head of North 
Ossetia declared. 

</TEXT>

